Note:
Comprehensive Test Suite for AI-Driven Memory Tuning Module

Tests all functionality of the AI-driven memory tuning and optimization system including:
- Workload analysis and profiling for memory optimization
- Auto-configuration of allocators and garbage collectors
- Adaptive optimization based on real-time usage patterns
- ML-based memory optimization and prediction
- AI/agent-friendly tuning APIs and integration
- Performance benchmarks for memory optimization decisions
- Error handling and edge cases for AI tuning
- Production-ready enterprise memory tuning scenarios
:End Note

Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/memory/ai_tuning" as AITuning
Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/utilities/common" as Common

Note: Test Configuration Constants
Let TEST_WORKLOAD_SAMPLES be 100
Let TEST_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD be 0.8
Let TEST_OPTIMIZATION_ITERATIONS be 25
Let TEST_MEMORY_USAGE_MB be 1024

Note: Test Result Tracking
Let test_results be Dictionary[String, Boolean] containing
Let test_count be 0
Let passed_count be 0
Let failed_count be 0

Note: Helper Functions for Testing

Process called "run_test" that takes test_name as String and test_function as Function returns Boolean:
    Set test_count to test_count plus 1
    
    Try:
        Display message "Running test: " plus test_name
        Let result be test_function()
        
        If result:
            Set passed_count to passed_count plus 1
            Set test_results[test_name] to true
            Display message "  ✓ PASS: " plus test_name
        Otherwise:
            Set failed_count to failed_count plus 1
            Set test_results[test_name] to false
            Display message "  ✗ FAIL: " plus test_name
            
        Return result
        
    Catch error:
        Set failed_count to failed_count plus 1
        Set test_results[test_name] to false
        Display message "  ✗ ERROR: " plus test_name plus " - " plus error.message
        Return false

Process called "assert_true" that takes condition as Boolean and message as String returns Boolean:
    If not condition:
        Display message "    Assertion failed: " plus message
        Return false
    Return true

Process called "assert_equal" that takes actual as Any and expected as Any and message as String returns Boolean:
    If actual is not equal to expected:
        Display message "    Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Expected: " plus expected
        Display message "    Actual: " plus actual
        Return false
    Return true

Process called "assert_greater_than" that takes actual as Float and threshold as Float and message as String returns Boolean:
    If actual is not greater than threshold:
        Display message "    Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Expected > " plus threshold plus ", got " plus actual
        Return false
    Return true

Process called "assert_within_range" that takes value as Float and min_val as Float and max_val as Float and message as String returns Boolean:
    If value is less than min_val or value is greater than max_val:
        Display message "    Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Expected between " plus min_val plus " and " plus max_val plus ", got " plus value
        Return false
    Return true

Process called "create_mock_memory_stats" that takes allocation_rate as Float and gc_pressure as Float returns AITuning.MemoryStats:
    Return AITuning.MemoryStats with:
        total_allocated as (allocation_rate multiplied by 1000000)
        total_freed as (allocation_rate multiplied by 800000)
        current_usage as (allocation_rate multiplied by 200000)
        peak_usage as (allocation_rate multiplied by 500000)
        allocation_count as (allocation_rate multiplied by 10000)
        deallocation_count as (allocation_rate multiplied by 8000)
        gc_collections as (gc_pressure multiplied by 100)
        gc_time_ms as (gc_pressure multiplied by 500)
        fragmentation_ratio as (gc_pressure multiplied by 0.3)
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "create_mock_workload_profile" that takes workload_type as String returns AITuning.WorkloadProfile:
    Return AITuning.WorkloadProfile with:
        workload_type as workload_type
        allocation_pattern as "sequential"
        gc_pressure as 0.3
        fragmentation as 0.1
        metadata as dictionary containing "test_data" as true

Note: Unit Tests for AI Tuner Creation and Configuration

Process called "test_create_ai_tuner" returns Boolean:
    Let tuner_config be AITuning.AITunerConfig with:
        learning_rate as 0.01
        confidence_threshold as 0.8
        optimization_window as 1000
        enable_prediction as true
        
    Let ai_tuner be AITuning.create_ai_tuner with config as tuner_config
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (ai_tuner is not null) and message as "AI tuner should be created"
    Let result2 be assert_equal with actual as ai_tuner.config.learning_rate and expected as 0.01 and message as "Learning rate should be set correctly"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as ai_tuner.config.enable_prediction and message as "Prediction should be enabled"
    Let result4 be assert_true with condition as (ai_tuner.ml_model is not null) and message as "ML model should be initialized"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Process called "test_ai_tuner_workload_analysis" returns Boolean:
    Let ai_tuner be AITuning.create_ai_tuner with config as AITuning.default_config
    Let memory_stats be create_mock_memory_stats with allocation_rate as 100.0 and gc_pressure as 0.5
    
    Let workload_profile be AITuning.analyze_workload with tuner as ai_tuner and stats as memory_stats
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (workload_profile is not null) and message as "Workload profile should be generated"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (workload_profile.workload_type is not empty) and message as "Workload type should be classified"
    Let result3 be assert_within_range with value as workload_profile.gc_pressure and min_val as 0.0 and max_val as 1.0 and message as "GC pressure should be normalized"
    Let result4 be assert_within_range with value as workload_profile.fragmentation and min_val as 0.0 and max_val as 1.0 and message as "Fragmentation should be normalized"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Process called "test_auto_configure_allocator" returns Boolean:
    Let ai_tuner be AITuning.create_ai_tuner with config as AITuning.default_config
    Let workload_profile be create_mock_workload_profile with workload_type as "high_throughput"
    
    Let allocator_config be AITuning.auto_configure_allocator with tuner as ai_tuner and profile as workload_profile
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (allocator_config is not null) and message as "Allocator config should be generated"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (allocator_config.allocator_type is not empty) and message as "Allocator type should be specified"
    Let result3 be assert_greater_than with actual as allocator_config.pool_size and threshold as 0.0 and message as "Pool size should be positive"
    Let result4 be assert_true with condition as (allocator_config.optimization_hints is not empty) and message as "Optimization hints should be provided"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Process called "test_auto_configure_gc" returns Boolean:
    Let ai_tuner be AITuning.create_ai_tuner with config as AITuning.default_config
    Let workload_profile be create_mock_workload_profile with workload_type as "memory_intensive"
    
    Let gc_config be AITuning.auto_configure_gc with tuner as ai_tuner and profile as workload_profile
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (gc_config is not null) and message as "GC config should be generated"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (gc_config.gc_algorithm is not empty) and message as "GC algorithm should be specified"
    Let result3 be assert_greater_than with actual as gc_config.heap_size and threshold as 0.0 and message as "Heap size should be positive"
    Let result4 be assert_within_range with value as gc_config.trigger_threshold and min_val as 0.1 and max_val as 0.9 and message as "Trigger threshold should be reasonable"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Note: Unit Tests for Adaptive Optimization

Process called "test_adaptive_optimization" returns Boolean:
    Let ai_tuner be AITuning.create_ai_tuner with config as AITuning.default_config
    Let memory_stats be create_mock_memory_stats with allocation_rate as 75.0 and gc_pressure as 0.7
    
    Let optimization_action be AITuning.adaptive_optimize with tuner as ai_tuner and stats as memory_stats
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (optimization_action is not null) and message as "Optimization action should be generated"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (optimization_action.action_type is not empty) and message as "Action type should be specified"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as (optimization_action.parameters is not empty) and message as "Parameters should be provided"
    Let result4 be assert_true with condition as (optimization_action.expected_improvement is greater than 0.0) and message as "Expected improvement should be positive"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Process called "test_predictive_memory_management" returns Boolean:
    Let predictor_config be AITuning.PredictorConfig with:
        prediction_window as 60
        confidence_threshold as 0.75
        model_type as "neural_network"
        
    Let memory_predictor be AITuning.create_memory_predictor with config as predictor_config
    Let current_state be AITuning.get_current_memory_state()
    
    Let memory_prediction be AITuning.predict_memory_needs with predictor as memory_predictor and current_state as current_state
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (memory_prediction is not null) and message as "Memory prediction should be generated"
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as memory_prediction.estimated_allocations and threshold as 0.0 and message as "Estimated allocations should be positive"
    Let result3 be assert_within_range with value as memory_prediction.confidence and min_val as 0.0 and max_val as 1.0 and message as "Confidence should be normalized"
    Let result4 be assert_true with condition as (memory_prediction.recommended_gc_trigger is not empty) and message as "GC trigger recommendation should be provided"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Process called "test_adaptive_gc_scheduling" returns Boolean:
    Let gc_algorithm be AITuning.create_test_gc()
    Let predictor be AITuning.create_memory_predictor with config as AITuning.default_predictor_config
    
    Let initial_gc_count be gc_algorithm.collection_count
    AITuning.adaptive_gc_schedule with gc as gc_algorithm and predictor as predictor
    
    Note: Should either trigger GC or schedule it for later
    Let gc_triggered_or_scheduled be (gc_algorithm.collection_count is greater than initial_gc_count) or (gc_algorithm.scheduled_collections is greater than 0)
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as gc_triggered_or_scheduled and message as "GC should be triggered or scheduled"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (gc_algorithm.last_decision_metadata is not null) and message as "Decision metadata should be recorded"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Note: Unit Tests for ML Model Integration

Process called "test_ml_model_training" returns Boolean:
    Let ai_tuner be AITuning.create_ai_tuner with config as AITuning.default_config
    Let training_data be list containing
    
    For i from 0 to (TEST_WORKLOAD_SAMPLES minus 1):
        Let sample_stats be create_mock_memory_stats with allocation_rate as (i plus 1) and gc_pressure as (i multiplied by 0.01)
        Let training_data be training_data with sample_stats added
    
    Let training_result be AITuning.train_ml_model with tuner as ai_tuner and data as training_data
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as training_result.success and message as "ML model training should succeed"
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as training_result.accuracy and threshold as 0.7 and message as "Model accuracy should be reasonable"
    Let result3 be assert_greater_than with actual as ai_tuner.ml_model.training_iterations and threshold as 0.0 and message as "Training iterations should be recorded"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Process called "test_ml_model_inference" returns Boolean:
    Let ai_tuner be AITuning.create_ai_tuner with config as AITuning.default_config
    Let memory_stats be create_mock_memory_stats with allocation_rate as 50.0 and gc_pressure as 0.4
    
    Let ml_prediction be AITuning.predict_optimization with tuner as ai_tuner and stats as memory_stats
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (ml_prediction is not null) and message as "ML prediction should be generated"
    Let result2 be assert_within_range with value as ml_prediction.confidence and min_val as 0.0 and max_val as 1.0 and message as "Prediction confidence should be normalized"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as (ml_prediction.recommended_actions is not empty) and message as "Recommended actions should be provided"
    Let result4 be assert_greater_than with actual as ml_prediction.expected_performance_gain and threshold as 0.0 and message as "Expected performance gain should be positive"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Note: Unit Tests for Real-time Feedback System

Process called "test_ai_memory_feedback" returns Boolean:
    Let predictor be AITuning.create_memory_predictor with config as AITuning.default_predictor_config
    Let memory_stats be create_mock_memory_stats with allocation_rate as 80.0 and gc_pressure as 0.6
    
    Let feedback_report be AITuning.ai_memory_feedback with predictor as predictor and stats as memory_stats
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (feedback_report is not null) and message as "Feedback report should be generated"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (feedback_report.prediction is not null) and message as "Prediction should be included"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as (feedback_report.suggestions is not empty) and message as "Suggestions should be provided"
    Let result4 be assert_true with condition as (feedback_report.optimization_score is greater than 0.0) and message as "Optimization score should be positive"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Process called "test_real_time_optimization_loop" returns Boolean:
    Let ai_tuner be AITuning.create_ai_tuner with config as AITuning.default_config
    Let optimization_loop be AITuning.create_optimization_loop with tuner as ai_tuner
    
    Let initial_performance be AITuning.get_current_performance_metrics()
    
    For i from 0 to (TEST_OPTIMIZATION_ITERATIONS minus 1):
        Let current_stats be AITuning.get_current_memory_stats()
        AITuning.optimization_loop_iteration with loop as optimization_loop and stats as current_stats
    
    Let final_performance be AITuning.get_current_performance_metrics()
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (optimization_loop.iterations is equal to TEST_OPTIMIZATION_ITERATIONS) and message as "All optimization iterations should complete"
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as optimization_loop.total_optimizations and threshold as 0.0 and message as "Some optimizations should be applied"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as (final_performance.overall_score is greater than or equal to initial_performance.overall_score) and message as "Performance should not degrade"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Note: Performance Tests

Process called "test_ai_tuning_performance" returns Boolean:
    Let ai_tuner be AITuning.create_ai_tuner with config as AITuning.default_config
    Let start_time be Common.get_current_time_ms()
    
    For i from 0 to 99:
        Let memory_stats be create_mock_memory_stats with allocation_rate as (i plus 1) and gc_pressure as (i multiplied by 0.01)
        Let workload_profile be AITuning.analyze_workload with tuner as ai_tuner and stats as memory_stats
        Let optimization_action be AITuning.adaptive_optimize with tuner as ai_tuner and stats as memory_stats
    
    Let end_time be Common.get_current_time_ms()
    Let total_time_ms be end_time minus start_time
    Let avg_time_per_analysis be total_time_ms divided by 100
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (total_time_ms is greater than 0.0) and message as "Performance test should take measurable time"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (avg_time_per_analysis is less than 10.0) and message as "Average analysis time should be reasonable"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Process called "test_memory_prediction_accuracy" returns Boolean:
    Let predictor be AITuning.create_memory_predictor with config as AITuning.default_predictor_config
    Let accurate_predictions be 0
    Let total_predictions be 20
    
    For i from 0 to (total_predictions minus 1):
        Let current_state be AITuning.create_mock_memory_state with base_allocation as (i multiplied by 1000)
        Let prediction be AITuning.predict_memory_needs with predictor as predictor and current_state as current_state
        
        Note: Simulate actual memory usage and compare with prediction
        Let actual_allocations be (i multiplied by 1000) plus (i multiplied by 100)
        Let prediction_error be abs(prediction.estimated_allocations minus actual_allocations) divided by actual_allocations
        
        If prediction_error is less than 0.2:
            Set accurate_predictions to accurate_predictions plus 1
    
    Let accuracy_rate be accurate_predictions divided by total_predictions
    
    Let result1 be assert_greater_than with actual as accuracy_rate and threshold as 0.6 and message as "Prediction accuracy should be reasonable"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (total_predictions is equal to 20) and message as "All predictions should be tested"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Note: Error Handling Tests

Process called "test_invalid_memory_stats_handling" returns Boolean:
    Let ai_tuner be AITuning.create_ai_tuner with config as AITuning.default_config
    
    Note: Test with null stats
    Let null_result be AITuning.analyze_workload with tuner as ai_tuner and stats as null
    
    Note: Test with negative values
    Let invalid_stats be AITuning.MemoryStats with:
        total_allocated as -1000
        total_freed as -500
        current_usage as -100
        peak_usage as -200
        allocation_count as -50
        deallocation_count as -40
        gc_collections as -10
        gc_time_ms as -100.0
        fragmentation_ratio as -0.5
        metadata as dictionary containing
    
    Let invalid_result be AITuning.analyze_workload with tuner as ai_tuner and stats as invalid_stats
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (null_result is null) and message as "Null stats should be handled gracefully"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (invalid_result is null) and message as "Invalid stats should be rejected"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as (AITuning.get_last_error() is not null) and message as "Error should be recorded"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Process called "test_ml_model_failure_recovery" returns Boolean:
    Let ai_tuner be AITuning.create_ai_tuner with config as AITuning.default_config
    
    Note: Simulate ML model failure
    AITuning.simulate_ml_model_failure with tuner as ai_tuner
    
    Let memory_stats be create_mock_memory_stats with allocation_rate as 60.0 and gc_pressure as 0.5
    Let fallback_result be AITuning.adaptive_optimize with tuner as ai_tuner and stats as memory_stats
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (fallback_result is not null) and message as "Fallback optimization should work"
    Let result2 be assert_equal with actual as fallback_result.optimization_method and expected as "heuristic_fallback" and message as "Should use heuristic fallback"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as ai_tuner.using_fallback_mode and message as "Should be in fallback mode"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Note: Integration Tests

Process called "test_end_to_end_ai_optimization" returns Boolean:
    Let ai_tuner be AITuning.create_ai_tuner with config as AITuning.default_config
    Let memory_system be AITuning.create_mock_memory_system()
    
    Note: Initial baseline performance
    Let baseline_performance be AITuning.measure_system_performance with system as memory_system
    
    Note: Apply AI tuning
    Let memory_stats be AITuning.get_memory_stats with system as memory_system
    Let workload_profile be AITuning.analyze_workload with tuner as ai_tuner and stats as memory_stats
    Let allocator_config be AITuning.auto_configure_allocator with tuner as ai_tuner and profile as workload_profile
    Let gc_config be AITuning.auto_configure_gc with tuner as ai_tuner and profile as workload_profile
    
    AITuning.apply_allocator_config with system as memory_system and config as allocator_config
    AITuning.apply_gc_config with system as memory_system and config as gc_config
    
    Note: Measure performance after optimization
    Let optimized_performance be AITuning.measure_system_performance with system as memory_system
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (workload_profile is not null) and message as "Workload analysis should succeed"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (allocator_config is not null) and message as "Allocator configuration should be generated"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as (gc_config is not null) and message as "GC configuration should be generated"
    Let result4 be assert_true with condition as (optimized_performance.throughput is greater than or equal to baseline_performance.throughput) and message as "Performance should not degrade"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Note: Test Runner

Process called "run_all_ai_tuning_tests" returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Display "Starting AI Tuning comprehensive test suite..."
    
    Note: AI Tuner Creation Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_create_ai_tuner" and test_function as test_create_ai_tuner
    run_test with test_name as "test_ai_tuner_workload_analysis" and test_function as test_ai_tuner_workload_analysis
    run_test with test_name as "test_auto_configure_allocator" and test_function as test_auto_configure_allocator
    run_test with test_name as "test_auto_configure_gc" and test_function as test_auto_configure_gc
    
    Note: Adaptive Optimization Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_adaptive_optimization" and test_function as test_adaptive_optimization
    run_test with test_name as "test_predictive_memory_management" and test_function as test_predictive_memory_management
    run_test with test_name as "test_adaptive_gc_scheduling" and test_function as test_adaptive_gc_scheduling
    
    Note: ML Model Integration Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_ml_model_training" and test_function as test_ml_model_training
    run_test with test_name as "test_ml_model_inference" and test_function as test_ml_model_inference
    
    Note: Real-time Feedback Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_ai_memory_feedback" and test_function as test_ai_memory_feedback
    run_test with test_name as "test_real_time_optimization_loop" and test_function as test_real_time_optimization_loop
    
    Note: Performance Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_ai_tuning_performance" and test_function as test_ai_tuning_performance
    run_test with test_name as "test_memory_prediction_accuracy" and test_function as test_memory_prediction_accuracy
    
    Note: Error Handling Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_invalid_memory_stats_handling" and test_function as test_invalid_memory_stats_handling
    run_test with test_name as "test_ml_model_failure_recovery" and test_function as test_ml_model_failure_recovery
    
    Note: Integration Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_end_to_end_ai_optimization" and test_function as test_end_to_end_ai_optimization
    
    Display "AI Tuning test suite completed."
    Display "Results: " plus passed_count plus " passed, " plus failed_count plus " failed, " plus test_count plus " total"
    
    Return Dictionary[String, Any] with:
        "total_tests" as test_count
        "passed_tests" as passed_count
        "failed_tests" as failed_count
        "success_rate" as (passed_count divided by test_count)
        "test_results" as test_results

Note: Main execution
Process called "main":
    Let results be run_all_ai_tuning_tests()
    Return results

Note: Execute tests when module is run
Let main_result be main()